<item>
            <title>[LU-9165] MDS handling of PFL layout initialization</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9165</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This work tracked the MDS handling of PFL layout object initialization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Initialize the OST objects of the 1st component of&#160;the PFL when its data are&#160;being created or its layout being set.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When the client tries to write beyond OST-object-initialized extent range, it will issue an IT_LAYOUT_MOD intent lock RPC, indicating the end offset of the write range, MDS needs to handle this RPC to allocate all OST objects of components covering this range.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MDS also needs to handle the replay of IT_LAYOUT_MOD RPC, which contains the current layout objects which the client knows, so that MDS won&apos;t allocate those OST objects again.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
